<div class="faq-wrap">
  <h1>Frequently asked questions about Luxury Property Care in Madeira</h1>
  <p class="subline">Our clear main focus is the long-term supervision of high-end properties for international owners. In addition, we offer selected optional services that can be combined depending on the property and the owner's needs.</p>

  <section class="faq-section">
<h2 class="sectionTitle">Property Care</h2>
    <p class="sectionIntro">Property Care is the largest and most important service area. It covers the ongoing supervision of high-end villas and apartments in Madeira.</p>
    <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question" type="button">What exactly does your Property Care service in Madeira include?</button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Property Care covers the structured supervision of high-end properties while the owners are away. This includes regular inspections, monitoring of the overall condition, attention to important areas inside and outside the home and reliable preparation before the owners return.</p></div></div>
    <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question" type="button">What kind of properties is Property Care intended for?</button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Our Property Care service is intended for luxury villas, modern sea-view residences and high-quality apartments that are not occupied year-round. It is especially relevant for international owners using Madeira as a second-home destination.</p></div></div>
    <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question" type="button">How often is my property inspected?</button><div class="faq-answer"><p>The inspection frequency is adapted to the property, its location and the way it is used. A coastal villa in an exposed position may require a different rhythm than an apartment in a more protected setting.</p></div></div>
    <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question" type="button">What happens if something is noticed during my absence?</button><div class="faq-answer"><p>If something relevant is identified during an inspection, we inform the owner in a structured and timely way so that appropriate next steps can be discussed.</p></div></div>
    <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question" type="button">Is the property prepared before my arrival?</button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. Preparing the property before the owners return is a central part of our Property Care concept. The goal is to ensure that the home feels calm, maintained and ready to use on arrival.</p></div></div>
  </section>

  <section class="faq-section">
    <h2 class="sectionTitle">Services</h2>
    <p class="sectionIntro">Services are optional add-ons. They complement Property Care whenever owners want additional preparation, care or support beyond the ongoing supervision of the property.</p>
    <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question" type="button">What additional services do you offer?</button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Our services include selected add-ons around high-end properties, such as extra preparation before stays, structured checks of specific areas and premium care that matches the standard of a private residence.</p></div></div>
    <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question" type="button">Can services be booked without Property Care?</button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Services are primarily designed as a complement to Property Care. In combination, they create the clearest and most reliable structure for owners who want both ongoing supervision and selected additional support.</p></div></div>
    <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question" type="button">Are services available regularly or only when needed?</button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Both options are possible. Some owners request them only before specific stays, while others prefer recurring add-on services depending on the property and their expectations.</p></div></div>
  </section>

  <section class="faq-section">
    <h2 class="sectionTitle">Storm Check</h2>
    <p class="sectionIntro">Storm Check is an optional additional service for owners who want an extra targeted inspection after more demanding weather conditions.</p>
    <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question" type="button">What is a storm check?</button><div class="faq-answer"><p>A storm check is a focused additional inspection related to stronger weather situations. It concentrates especially on exterior areas that may be more affected by wind or heavy rain.</p></div></div>
    <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question" type="button">When does a storm check make sense?</button><div class="faq-answer"><p>It is particularly useful for exposed hillside villas, coastal homes or properties with large outdoor areas, especially when owners are away and want an added level of reassurance.</p></div></div>
    <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question" type="button">Is a storm check automatically included in Property Care?</button><div class="faq-answer"><p>No. Storm Check is defined as an optional add-on. Property Care remains the main service, while Storm Check is available whenever an owner wants an additional targeted control.</p></div></div>
  </section>

  <section class="faq-section">
    <h2 class="sectionTitle">Alojamento Local</h2>
    <p class="sectionIntro">Alojamento Local is also an additional service area. Our primary focus remains Luxury Property Care for private high-end residences. AL support is offered only for selected properties where the quality level fits the project.</p>
    <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question" type="button">Do you also support Alojamento Local properties in Madeira?</button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes, but not as the main focus of our business. We support selected Alojamento Local properties when the object, quality expectations and workflow fit our way of working.</p></div></div>
    <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question" type="button">Which services are included in the AL area?</button><div class="faq-answer"><p>The AL area focuses on structured preparation between stays, careful cleaning, quality control and a reliable overall standard for selected high-end holiday properties.</p></div></div>
    <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question" type="button">Is Alojamento Local a main business focus for you?</button><div class="faq-answer"><p>No. The clear main focus remains Luxury Property Care for international owners of private residences. Alojamento Local is an additional optional service for selected properties.</p></div></div>
    <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question" type="button">Can Alojamento Local be combined with Property Care?</button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes, that can make sense when a property is used partly as a private residence and partly for holiday guests. In such cases the structure must be especially clear and reliable.</p></div></div>
  </section>
</div>

